register.description: This register contains the IP revision code
This register controls the various parameters of the OCP interface. Note that most fields are read-only.

bitfield.description: Slave interface power management (IDLE request/acknowledgement control).

bitenum.description: Force-idle. IDLE request is acknowledged unconditionally and immediately.
No-idle. IDLE request is never acknowledged.
Smart-idle. IDLE request acknowledgement is based on the internal module activity.
Reserved. Do not use.
Wakeup generation is disabled.
Wakeup generation is enabled.
No action
Start soft reset sequence
Interface clock is not gated when the interface is idle.
Automatic internal OCP clock gating strategy is applied, based on the OCP interface activity.
